To quantify the amount of H2O2 produced, we carried out an independent test not based on electrochemical methods: permanganate titration. Typically, samples with a volume of 1 mL collected at certain time intervals were diluted into 10 mL and titrated with 0.005 M KMnO4 aqueous solution. The concentration of H2O2 produced was calculated according to the following equation:2CH2O2=5CKMnO4×VKMnO4÷2VH2O2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
